ia Pizza Sauce');\">Print or download (PDF)</a></div>\n</div>\n<ul class=\"breadcrumbs\">\n<li><a href=\"/\">Home</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/\">Recipes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/recipes/pizza/\"><span itemprop=\"recipeCategory\">Pizza</span></a></li>\n<li>Neighborhood Pizzeria Pizza Sauce</li>\n</ul>\n<div itemprop=\"description\" class=\"description\">Although I love the rich flavor of my chunky <a href='/recipes/san-marzano-pizza-sauce/'>San Marzano pizza sauce</a>, it gets expensive quick if you're trying to make pizza for a crowd. This recipe uses a third of the tomatoes and is ready in five minutes. It's silky smooth and the balsamic vinegar gives it a subtle tang that will have you coming back for seconds.</div>\n<div class=\"stats\">\n<ul>\n<li>Prep: <meta itemprop=\"prepTime\" value=\"PT5M\"/>5 min</li>\n<li>Total: <meta itemprop=\"totalTime\" value=\"PT5M\"/>5 min</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeYield\">Yields 2 cups (enough for 4-6 pizzas)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"steps\">\n<div class=\"right\">\n<a href=\"/recipes/neighborhood-pizzeria-pizza-sauce/neighborhood-pizzeria-pizza-sauce_large.jpg\"><img class=\"polaroid\" src=\"/recipes/neighborhood-pizzeria-pizza-sauce/neighborhood-pizzeria-pizza-sauce.jpg\" alt=\"Neighborhood Pizzeria Pizza Sauce\" itemprop=\"image\"/></a>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">28 ounce can whole or diced tomatoes</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">3 cloves garlic, roughly chopped or minced</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">6 fresh basil leaves or 2 teaspoons dried basil</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">3 teaspoons olive oil</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">1 teaspoon balsamic vinegar, or to taste</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">&frac12; teaspoon sea salt</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\">1/8 teaspoon pepper</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">Blend the tomatoes, garlic, olive oil, balsamic vinegar, basil, salt, and pepper in a food processor or blender.</li>\n<li class=\"direction\">This keeps up to a week in the fridge or several months in the freezer.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"footnote\">\n<div class=\"logo\">MakeBetterFood.com</div>\nFrom MakeBetterFood.com. <time itemprop=\"datePublished\" datetime=\"2012-10-29\">Oct 29, 2012</time>. (http://makebetterfood.com/recipes/neighborhood-pizzeria-pizza-sauce/). Adapted from <a href='http://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-diy-pizz-13507'>The Kitchn</a>.\n</div>\n<!-- Microformat Ingredients -->\n<ul class=\"hidden\">\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">28 ounce can whole or diced tomatoes</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">3 cloves garlic, roughly chopped or minced</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">6 fresh basil leaves or 2 teaspoons dried basil</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">3 teaspoons olive oil</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">1 teaspoon balsamic vinegar, or to taste</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac12; teaspoon sea salt</li>\n<li itemprop=\"ingredients\">1/8 teaspoon pepper</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- Microformat Steps -->\n<ol class=\"hidden\">\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Blend the tomatoes, garlic, olive oil, balsamic vinegar, basil, salt, and pepper in a food processor or blender.</li>\n<li itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">This keeps up to a week in the fridge or several months in the freezer.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"notPrinted\">\n<div class=\"grid_12\">\n<div class=\"recipe\">\n<h4>Related Equipment or Ingredients</h4>\n<div class=\"pushTop10 clearfix polarioidSummaryRow\">\n<div class=\"polaroidSummary\">\n<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Cuisinart-DLC-10S-Classic-7-Cup-Processor/dp/B00004S9EM?SubscriptionId=AKIAJT76QZNN5CAIGPSQ&tag=makbetfoo-20&linkCode=xm2&camp=2025&creative=165953&creativeASIN=B00004S9EM\"><img src=\"http://ecx.images-amazon.com/images/I/416SMU4gPKL.SL100_AA105.jpg\" alt=\"Cuisinart Food Processor\" class=\"\"/>\nCuisinart Food Processor</a>\n</div>\n<div class=\"polaroidSummary\">\n<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/OXO-Grips-4-Inch-Pizza-Wheel/dp/B00004OCJN?SubscriptionId=AKIAJT76QZNN5CAIGPSQ&tag=m